article.headline: Campbell 90, Lipscomb 84
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Derek Gray scored 21 points and Tarick Johnson added 21 points and 13 rebounds to lead Campbell to a 90-84 win against Lipscomb on Saturday. It was just the second victory of the season for the Camels (2-17, 2-10 Atlantic Sun), who made 36-of-43 free throws. Campbell's Diego Aguiar and Dominique Klein had 14 points each. Brian Fisk paced Lipscomb (5-14, 2-9) with 26 points and six assists. James Poindexter also had 17 points for the Bisons. Campbell led by as many as 14 points before settling for a 45-33 lead at halftime. Johnson had 18 in the first half. Lipscomb pulled to within 62-59 with 9:17 left but Johnson had a jumper to help stave off the comeback. Campbell played without second-leading scorer Anthony Atkinson, who was suspended because of a violation of team policy. The win was the 300th in NCAA Division I for the Camels.
